{"title": "Homilies on Colossians", "description": "\"Holy indeed are all the Epistles of Paul: but some advantage have those which he sent after he was in bonds: those, for instance, to the Ephesians and Philemon: that to Timothy, that to the Philippians, and the one before us: for this also was sent when he was a prisoner,\u2026\n<br><br>\n\"But why do I say that these Epistles have some advantage over the rest in this respect, because he writes while in bonds? As if a champion were to write in the midst of carnage and victory; so also in truth did he. For himself too was aware that this was a great thing, for writing to Philemon he saith, \u201cWhom I have begotten in my bonds.\u201d\n<br><br>\n\"And this he said, that we should not be dispirited when in adversity, but even rejoice.\" (St John Chrysostom, from Homily 1)", "duration": 24895, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2129", "name": "St. John Chrysostom"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/homilies_on_colossians_2103_librivox/homilies_colossians_2103.jpg", "copyright_year": "1886", "genres": ["Christianity - Commentary"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "A LibriVox Volunteer"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "A LibriVox Volunteer"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Magdalene Miller"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Homily 1 Col 1:1-8", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/homilies_on_colossians_2103_librivox/homiliesoncolossians_01_chrysostom_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2502}, {"section": 2, "title": "Homily 2 Col 1:9-15", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/homilies_on_colossians_2103_librivox/homiliesoncolossians_02_chrysostom_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2523}, {"section": 3, "title": "Homily 3 Col 1:15-20", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/homilies_on_colossians_2103_librivox/homiliesoncolossians_03_chrysostom_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1882}, {